  "supported_languages": "English",
  "reviews": "<p>\"Advice for playing Starseed Pilgrim: As long as you still have questions, continue.\"<br> &ndash; <a href=\"https://twitter.com/Jonathan_Blow/status/312041543764701184\">Jonathan Blow</a></p>\n\n<p>\"Unfortunately, you cannot talk about Starseed Pilgrim, because that would spoil it for so many others. There’s unwritten rules at play. But it’s so open to discussion between two or more journeyers who find themselves at similar junctions.\"<br> &ndash; <a href=\"http://indiestatik.com/2013/03/15/starseed-pilgrim/\">Indie Statik</a></p>\n\n<p>\"It’s OK to feel lost, it seems to suggest, because it’s the only way to feel the intoxicating effect of discovery. I became so angry with Starseed Pilgrim because it purposely allows you, encourages you even, to feel lost.<br>&ndash; <a href=\"http://gamechurch.com/embracing-the-rabbit-hole-in-starseed-pilgrim/\">Game Church</a></p>\n\n\n",
