  "reviews": "“Zordon may have wanted &quot;teens with attitude,&quot; but Chroma Squad and its unabashed, utterly geeky love-in for all things tokusatsu shows something even harder to find: A game with heart and soul. That heart shines through the rough edges, and in some ways even turns them to its advantage.”<br>8/10 – <a href=\"http://www.destructoid.com/review-chroma-squad-291251.phtml\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\"  >Destructoid</a><br><br>“Chroma Squad is terrifically enjoyable. Fans of tactical RPGs will have oodles of fun, and those who also look fondly upon the youthful days of the Power Rangers will get an extra kick.”<br>8/10 – <a href=\"https://steamcommunity.com/linkfilter/?url=http://www.twinfinite.net/2015/05/04/chroma-squad-review/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"  >Twinfinite</a><br><br>“The greatest Power Rangers game there never was.”<br><a href=\"http://www.rockpapershotgun.com/2015/05/15/chroma-squad-review/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\"  >Rock Paper Shotgun</a><br>",
